   the CG stress. Results: Majority of the CGs (74.62\%) were females. 65\%
   of CGs graded their burden as moderate to severe. 81\% of CGs had left
   their work for caregiving. More than half of the CGs felt sleep
   disturbance and physical strain. Psychological instability and financial
   burdens were reported in 3/4th of CGs. Group A CGs faced more sleep,
   financial, health, and social life disturbance. Patient's bladder and
   bowel problems, shoulder pain, patients noncooperative attitude for
   medication administration, and physiotherapy were more upsetting for
