   knowledge test and the admission scores in the Mini Mental State
   Examination of the patients was also revealed (F{[}1,51]=48.03-58.87, P
   < 0.01). In conclusion, the results suggest that there was an
   improvement in the acquisition of stroke-related knowledge by both
   patients with stroke, and their caregivers, after a stroke educational
   group. A further study exploring the behavioral changes of individuals
   with stroke and their caregivers; after attending a stroke educational
