   long-term implications of stroke and the caregiving role after
   completing the Preparedness Assessment for the Transition Home After
   Stroke (PATH-s). Design/Methods
   In this qualitative study, cognitive interviews were conducted with 20
   stroke caregivers who completed the PATH-s tool as part of an instrument
   validation study. Data were analyzed for salient themes related to their
   perceptions about stroke and the caregiving role. Findings
