Abstract = {Objectives: Understand the needs and feelings of the caregiver of
   individuals who have experienced a stroke, and identify the information
   provided to these caregivers by health professionals. Methods: This
   exploratory, descriptive qualitative approach used semistructured
   interviews to understand the experience of six caregivers, during the
   period from May to August, 2008. The data from these interviews were
   analyzed using discourse analysis. Results: Three categories were
   identified: the initial needs of the caregiver, the caregiver and
   his/her feelings, and the guidance received by the caregiver from health
   professionals. Needs of the caregivers were varied, but primarily
   concerned adaptive difficulties. Diverse feelings were identified,
   including ambivalence, and a range of intensity of those feelings was
   noted. Guidelines provided by health professionals ranged from a total
   absence of information, to guidance that was felt by caregivers to meet
   all of their needs. Conclusions: There is need for discussion regarding
   provision of standardized guidelines for caregivers, and a strategy to
   support caregivers and patients.},
