   years, and the mean age of primary caregivers was 57.60 years.
   Interventions: Not applicable.
   Methods: The Family Assessment Device (FAD) and Center for Epidemiologic
   Studies Depression Scale (CES-D), respectively, were used.
   Results: Following a stroke of a family member, 71\% of caregivers
   experienced depressive symptoms. Higher depression severity in
   caregivers was linked to caregiver education, stroke survivor ADLs, and
   family functioning.
