   clinicians (N = 8; N = 4), and technology experts (N = 4; N = 4).
   Rigorous qualitative content analysis procedures were used with
   descriptive statistics for ratings. Findings Qualitative strengths and
   areas for improvement refined the goal-setting tip sheet. From 1 =
   strongly disagree to 5 = strongly agree, ratings averaged from 3.25 to
   5.00 for strategies, accuracy, feasibility, and acceptability.
   Conclusions The goal-setting tip sheet was found to be accurate,
   feasible, and acceptable. Future research is needed to determine the
   impact on caregiver health.},
