Abstract = {The aims of this project were to explore the needs of family caregivers
   in the Chinese-American community and to develop training videos for
   caregivers on dressing stroke survivors. In-depth, semi-structured,
   open-ended interviews were used to explore the problems of caregivers of
   stroke survivors. Forty participants were recruited from
   Chinese-American communities. Verbatim interview transcripts were coded
   and analyzed. Four main concerns emerged: the impact and adjustment in
   lifestyle for family caregivers; lack of social activities and failure
   to seek community support; physical and mental stress and methods to
   alleviate stress, such as instruction in heavy lifting and guidance for
   daily activities, which include dressing. An 18-min video was produced
   to provide instruction on dressing stroke survivors for those who need
   this information. Also, this article addresses the lack of social
