   caregiver burden using Zarit Burden Inventory (ZBI) was collected. One
   hundred one participants were assessed. The mean ZBI was 21.6 +/- 14.5
   {[}95\% CI, 18.7-24.8]. More than half of caregivers reported no burden
   (54.5\%). High burdens were associated with low self-reported income,
   high numbers of basic activities of daily living needed and coexisting
   musculoskeletal conditions. The observed low degree of burden might be
   the result of the sociocultural view of the study participants.},
